FBIS3-16988 "drsov055_a_94006" FBIS-SOV-94-055 Document Type:Daily Report 21 Mar 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Further on Japanese Foreign Minister Hata's Visit Hata Wants DPRK To Permit Inspections AU2103143694 Paris AFP in English 1430 GMT 21 Mar 94 AU2103143694 Paris AFP Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Moscow, March 21 (AFP) -- Japanese Foreign Minister Tsutomu Hata demanded Monday that North Korea let international experts carry out a full inspection of its nuclear facilities and criticized Pyonyang's renewed threat to pull out of the Nuclear non- Proliferation Treaty (NPT). "Japan is worried by the fact that we could not obtain confirmation of the non-use by North Korea of nuclear materials for military purposes," Hata said at a news conference.
